      "content": "Focus your search on discrepancies in the telemetry data related to power fluctuations or unexpected environmental readings during those visual gaps. Anomalies in the recorded radio signals, specifically those that don't correlate with known equipment performance, could indicate external interference or unknown phenomena. Look for deviations in the expected gravitational readings or sensor data that seem too perfect or too erratic for a standard lunar environment. These subtle technical inconsistencies are often where the real, unedited story hides.",
